3️⃣ Key Difference (Interview Table)
Concept	L1 (Lasso)	L2 (Ridge)
Penalty	(	w
Gradient	sign(w)	2w
Effect	Some weights → 0	All weights shrink
Feature Selection	Yes	No
4️⃣ Intuition

L2 (Ridge)
👉 Smooth shrinkage
👉 All features remain

L1 (Lasso)
👉 Sharp shrinkage
👉 Some features removed

5️⃣ Python Example
from sklearn.linear_model import Lasso, Ridge

lasso = Lasso(alpha=0.1)
ridge = Ridge(alpha=0.1)

lasso.fit(X_train, y_train)
ridge.fit(X_train, y_train)

print("Lasso Coeff:", lasso.coef_)
print("Ridge Coeff:", ridge.coef_)

✅ Perfect Interview Answer (2 lines)

In Ridge (L2), gradient adds 2λw, which shrinks coefficients smoothly.
In Lasso (L1), gradient adds λ sign(w), which can push coefficients exactly to zero, performing feature selection.